    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "Offered is an exceptional 996.2 Carrera 4S, featuring the M96.03 3.6L flat-six engine mated to a precise G96/01 six-speed manual transaxle. This example is in concours-grade state, with the IMS bearing proactively addressed via an LN Engineering retrofit and the Rear Main Seal (RMS) verified dry. The wide-body chassis retains factory-spec alignment geometry, utilizing the original AWD viscous coupling for optimal torque distribution. Braking performance is anchored by four-piston monoblock calipers over cross-drilled rotors with no evidence of thermal stress. The undercarriage retains its factory cosmoline coating, and the interior demonstrates zero bolster compression or UV degradation. Every bushing, vacuum line, and electronic actuator functions within original factory tolerances, ensuring linear power delivery and the telepathic steering feedback synonymous with the platform.",
